	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Nov 15th 9:35 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.93]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Greetings Jcasetnl,<br><br>My understanding of the way spell resists work is it all hinges on the level of the Caster.&nbsp;&nbsp;If you try to cast on any mob that is more than 5 levels higher than you are, more than likely the spell will be resisted. The level of the spell you are using isn't factored in.  Now that is my understanding....someone correct me if I'm wrong.<br><br>For example, I still root level 45+ mobs with my level 22 Root spell and stun them with my level 30 stun spell.  No problem.  I am level 53. So the need to use a more powerful spell isn't necessary.  Lower level spells like Flash of Light, etc. will still work fine due to my level...not the level of the spell. <br><br>However, when trying to cure disease, cure poison or the like...the level and the power of the spell can make a huge difference in the number of casts it takes to cure your target.  Nasty DOTs like Trakanon's poison DoT or Talendor's Heat DoT can be very hard to cure and many players still die even after the Dragon has been killed, because of the DoT. It takes powerful spells to cure these DoTs but that's because they came from a level 60+ mob!<br><br>Hope this helps!<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Cavalier<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"<br>&nbsp;<br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
